* 1.3 What is the nature of truth?

** 1.3.1 What makes a statement true?

*** 1.3.1.1 Catholic Response
Statements achieve truth through correspondence with reality and divine revelation, requiring adequate intellect conforming to being and supernatural faith according to Thomistic correspondence theory.

*** 1.3.1.2 Protestant Response
Statements achieve truth through conformity to Scripture as ultimate authority, requiring faithful interpretation and Holy Spirit illumination according to Reformed theological epistemology.

*** 1.3.1.3 Orthodox Response
Statements achieve truth through participation in divine energies and patristic consensus, requiring spiritual discernment and traditional wisdom according to Orthodox theological epistemology.

*** 1.3.1.4 Jewish Response
Statements achieve truth through Torah interpretation and rabbinic consensus, requiring scholarly investigation and traditional authority according to Jewish hermeneutical tradition.

*** 1.3.1.5 Islamic Response
Statements achieve truth through Quranic revelation and prophetic tradition, requiring authentic transmission and scholarly interpretation according to Islamic epistemological framework.

*** 1.3.1.6 Hindu Response
Statements achieve truth through scriptural authority (shabda), direct perception (pratyaksha), and inference (anumana), requiring valid means of knowledge according to Vedantic epistemological theory.

*** 1.3.1.7 Buddhist Response
Statements achieve conventional truth through conceptual designation and ultimate truth through emptiness realization, requiring understanding of two-truth theory according to Madhyamaka philosophy.

*** 1.3.1.8 Confucian Response
Statements achieve truth through moral correctness and cultural authenticity, requiring virtue cultivation and scholarly wisdom according to Confucian understanding of moral truth.

*** 1.3.1.9 Platonic Response
Statements achieve truth through correspondence with eternal forms and dialectical reasoning, requiring philosophical education and intellectual purification according to Platonic epistemological framework.

*** 1.3.1.10 Pragmatic Response
