** 1.3.2 Is truth absolute or relative?

*** 1.3.2.1 Catholic Response
Truth remains absolute as divine attribute participating in eternal law, with relative human understanding requiring supernatural revelation and magisterial guidance according to Thomistic theological epistemology.

*** 1.3.2.2 Protestant Response
Truth remains absolute in Scripture while human interpretation requires humility and faithful submission to divine revelation according to Reformed understanding of biblical authority.

*** 1.3.2.3 Orthodox Response
Truth remains absolute in divine energies while human participation varies through spiritual development and patristic guidance according to Orthodox theological framework.

*** 1.3.2.4 Jewish Response
Truth remains absolute in Torah while interpretation develops through rabbinic discussion and scholarly investigation according to Jewish hermeneutical tradition.

*** 1.3.2.5 Islamic Response
Truth remains absolute in Quranic revelation while human understanding develops through scholarly interpretation (ijtihad) according to Islamic epistemological framework.

*** 1.3.2.6 Hindu Response
Truth remains absolute as Brahman (sat-chit-ananda) while manifestations appear relative through maya, requiring spiritual realization to transcend relative understanding according to Advaita Vedanta.

*** 1.3.2.7 Buddhist Response
Truth encompasses both conventional (sammuti-sacca) and ultimate (paramattha-sacca) dimensions, requiring understanding of emptiness and dependent origination according to Buddhist two-truth theory.

*** 1.3.2.8 Confucian Response
Truth remains absolute in cosmic principle (li) while cultural expressions vary through historical development, requiring virtue cultivation and scholarly wisdom according to Neo-Confucian framework.

*** 1.3.2.9 Platonic Response
Truth remains absolute in eternal forms while particular instances participate imperfectly, requiring philosophical education to transcend relative opinions according to Platonic epistemological hierarchy.

*** 1.3.2.10 Postmodern Response
Truth remains relative to cultural context and linguistic construction, requiring critical deconstruction of absolute claims according to postmodern epistemological critique.

*** 1.3.2.11 Roman Catholic Response
Truth remains absolute as divine attribute participating in eternal law while human understanding requires supernatural revelation and magisterial guidance, with relative cultural expressions serving absolute truth according to Thomistic framework.

*** 1.3.2.12 Eastern Catholic Response
Truth remains absolute in divine energies while human participation varies through spiritual development and liturgical tradition, integrating Eastern understanding with Catholic unity according to Eastern Catholic synthesis.

*** 1.3.2.13 Traditional Catholic Response
Truth remains absolutely immutable through perennial philosophy and traditional doctrine, requiring resistance to relativist errors and modernist innovations according to traditional Catholic framework.

*** 1.3.2.14 Catholic Religious Orders Response
Truth remains absolute through contemplative realization while monastic expression varies through specific charisms, requiring integration of universal truth with particular spiritual traditions.

*** 1.3.2.15 Contemporary Catholic Response
Truth remains absolute while requiring dialogue with contemporary understanding, integrating universal principles with cultural adaptation according to modern Catholic intellectual movements.

*** 1.3.2.16 Lutheran Response
Truth remains absolute in Scripture while human interpretation requires faithful submission to divine revelation, with cultural expressions serving biblical authority according to Lutheran theological framework.

*** 1.3.2.17 Reformed/Presbyterian Response
Truth remains absolutely sovereign through divine decree while human understanding suffers total depravity, requiring systematic theological framework and divine election according to Reformed understanding.

*** 1.3.2.18 Anglican/Episcopal Response
Truth remains absolute while requiring comprehensive synthesis of Scripture, tradition, and reason, balancing universal principles with via media adaptation according to Anglican methodology.

*** 1.3.2.19 Baptist Response
Truth remains absolute in Scripture while individual interpretation requires spiritual illumination, emphasizing biblical authority within congregational autonomy according to Baptist distinctives.

*** 1.3.2.20 Methodist/Wesleyan Response
Truth remains absolute while requiring quadrilateral synthesis of Scripture, tradition, reason, and experience, balancing universal principles with holistic engagement according to Wesleyan methodology.

*** 1.3.2.21 Eastern Orthodox Response
Truth remains absolute in divine energies while human participation develops through theosis and patristic guidance, requiring spiritual transformation according to Orthodox theological framework.

*** 1.3.2.22 Autocephalous Orthodox Response
Truth remains absolute in Orthodox doctrine while cultural expression varies through autocephalous governance, maintaining theological integrity within cultural distinctiveness according to canonical tradition.

*** 1.3.2.23 Orthodox Theological Schools Response
Truth remains absolute while requiring neo-patristic synthesis with contemporary scholarship, maintaining Orthodox integrity through academic engagement according to theological methodology.

*** 1.3.2.24 Orthodox Monastic Response
Truth remains absolute while achieved through hesychast prayer and ascetical discipline, requiring spiritual transformation and contemplative realization according to athonite wisdom.

*** 1.3.2.25 Orthodox Diaspora Response
Truth remains absolute in Orthodox tradition while cultural adaptation occurs in multicultural contexts, preserving theological principles through diaspora experience.

*** 1.3.2.26 Coptic Orthodox Response
Truth remains absolute in Incarnation according to Cyrilline christology while expressed through Egyptian Christian cultural identity, maintaining theological distinctiveness through historical experience.

*** 1.3.2.27 Ethiopian Orthodox Response
Truth remains absolute through Tewahedo christology while integrating biblical Judaism with apostolic Christianity, expressing universal truth through Ethiopian covenant according to Orthodox synthesis.

*** 1.3.2.28 Eritrean Orthodox Response
