** 1.3.3 Can we know truth with certainty?

*** 1.3.3.1 Catholic Response
Certainty achieves through divine revelation and rational demonstration, with supernatural faith providing higher certainty than natural reason according to Thomistic epistemological framework.

*** 1.3.3.2 Protestant Response
Certainty achieves through Scripture and Holy Spirit testimony, with faithful confidence transcending rational doubt according to Reformed epistemological understanding.

